---
// FAQ Section Component
---

<section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-gray-900" data-scroll-fade>
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-14">
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-white">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </div>

    <!-- Two FAQs only -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 items-start">
      <!-- FAQ 1: Who we work with -->
      <details class="group bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm open:bg-white/7">
        <summary class="list-none flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer select-none">
          <span class="text-white font-semibold">Who do we work with?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-300 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="mt-4 text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        We work with schools and colleges to guide students as they build their future.
        </div>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ 2: Why better than online platforms -->
      <details class="group bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm open:bg-white/7">
        <summary class="list-none flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer select-none">
          <span class="text-white font-semibold">Why are we better than online learning platforms?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-300 transition-transform duration-200 group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="mt-4 text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
       We are on-site, helping students actually understand things, rather than just ensuring they complete a course. We also introduce peer-to-peer (P2P) learning, where students learn with their friends, which helps them understand things better.
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>